{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "08", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "01", "M": "54", "S": "51"}}, "news": [{"title": "Bagmane Prime Office REIT IPO subscribed 23.71 times", "para": "Bagmane Prime Office REIT's initial public offer saw strong investor interest, closing with 23.71 times subscription. The Rs 3,405-crore IPO attracted over two lakh applications. Institutional investors subscribed 25.25 times, while other investors bid 21.87 times. The REIT secured Rs 1,150 crore from anchor investors. Proceeds will fund property acquisitions.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/commercial/bagmane-prime-office-reit-ipo-subscribed-23-71-times/130902921?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-76330/130902921.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "commercial"}, {"title": "Chhattisgarh offers 50% rebate on property registration for women", "para": "Chhattisgarh has announced a 50% rebate on property registration fees for properties registered in women's names, aiming to boost their economic security and social standing. Chief Minister Vishnu Deo Sai hailed the move as a historic step for women's empowerment, expecting long-term benefits to outweigh the revenue impact.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/chhattisgarh-government-launches-50-property-registration-rebate-for-women/130903141?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-22932/130903141.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Indiabulls Real Estate case: Four entities pay \u20b910.5 crore to Sebi as settlement", "para": "Market regulator Sebi settled a fund diversion case against four entities linked to the former Indiabulls Real Estate Ltd. The companies paid a total of Rs 10.49 crore to close the proceedings. This case involved allegations of fund diversion from Albasta Infrastructure Ltd to promoter-connected entities. Sebi investigated potential misuse of funds between FY10 and FY17.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/regulatory/indiabulls-real-estate-case-four-entities-pay-10-5-crore-to-sebi-as-settlement/130896983?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-109692/130896983.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "regulatory"}]}